ARM GAS  C:\Users\Nathan\AppData\Local\Temp\cc7B0wmf.s 			page 4


 145:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c **** 
 146:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       Use Functions HAL_QSPI_RegisterCallback() to register a user callback,
 147:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       it allows to register following callbacks:
 148:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) ErrorCallback : callback when error occurs.
 149:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) AbortCpltCallback : callback when abort is completed.
 150:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) FifoThresholdCallback : callback when the fifo threshold is reached.
 151:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) CmdCpltCallback : callback when a command without data is completed.
 152:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) RxCpltCallback : callback when a reception transfer is completed.
 153:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) TxCpltCallback : callback when a transmission transfer is completed.
 154:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) RxHalfCpltCallback : callback when half of the reception transfer is completed.
 155:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) TxHalfCpltCallback : callback when half of the transmission transfer is completed.
 156:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) StatusMatchCallback : callback when a status match occurs.
 157:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) TimeOutCallback : callback when the timeout perioed expires.
 158:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) MspInitCallback    : QSPI MspInit.
 159:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) MspDeInitCallback  : QSPI MspDeInit.
 160:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 161:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       and a pointer to the user callback function.
 162:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c **** 
 163:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       Use function HAL_QSPI_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 164:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       weak (overridden) function. It allows to reset following callbacks:
 165:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) ErrorCallback : callback when error occurs.
 166:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) AbortCpltCallback : callback when abort is completed.
 167:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) FifoThresholdCallback : callback when the fifo threshold is reached.
 168:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) CmdCpltCallback : callback when a command without data is completed.
 169:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) RxCpltCallback : callback when a reception transfer is completed.
 170:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) TxCpltCallback : callback when a transmission transfer is completed.
 171:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) RxHalfCpltCallback : callback when half of the reception transfer is completed.
 172:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) TxHalfCpltCallback : callback when half of the transmission transfer is completed.
 173:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) StatusMatchCallback : callback when a status match occurs.
 174:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) TimeOutCallback : callback when the timeout perioed expires.
 175:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) MspInitCallback    : QSPI MspInit.
 176:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****         (+) MspDeInitCallback  : QSPI MspDeInit.
 177:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       This function) takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle and the Callback ID.
 178:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c **** 
 179:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       By default, after the HAL_QSPI_Init and if the state is HAL_QSPI_STATE_RESET
 180:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       all callbacks are reset to the corresponding legacy weak (overridden) functions.
 181:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit callbacks that are respectively
 182:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       reset to the legacy weak (overridden) functions in the HAL_QSPI_Init
 183:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       and  HAL_QSPI_DeInit only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 184:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_QSPI_Init and HAL_QSPI_DeInit
 185:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
 186:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c **** 
 187:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in READY state only.
 188:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       Exception done for MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks that can be registered/unregistered
 189:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       in READY or RESET state, thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used
 190:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       during the Init/DeInit.
 191:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 192:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       using HAL_QSPI_RegisterCallback before calling HAL_QSPI_DeInit
 193:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       or HAL_QSPI_Init function.
 194:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c **** 
 195:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       When The compilation define USE_HAL_QSPI_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 196:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       not defined, the callback registering feature is not available
 197:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_qspi.c ****       and weak (overridden) callbacks are used.
